    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition">
                <div type="textpart">
                    <ab>In nomine Sancte et individue Trinitatis. <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/130">Henricus</persName> divina favente clemencia Romanorum
                            <rs key="#Emperor/king">imperator</rs> augustus. Si fervore caritatis
                        accensi de statu ac restauracione ecclesiarum Dei diligenti cura et
                        indagacione tractamus, regni nostri solium stabiliri, ac feliciter regnare
                        cum Christo nequaquam ambigimus. quo circa omnium fidelium Sancte Dei
                        Ecclesie, nostrorumque presencium ac futurorum devocio noverit, qualiter
                            <persName key="#Abbots" ref="#people/1992">Ylarius</persName>
                        <rs key="#Abbots">abbas</rs>
                        <rs key="#Monasteries">cenobii</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Monasteries #Abbots #Monks #Cells/hermitages #Immunity #Tolls #Exemption #Churches #Aldius #Landed_possessions #Mountains #Forests #Rivers #Riverbed #Castle #Animals #Hay/fodder #Villas #Mansi #Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Fish #Fisheries #Wine #Slave #Slave_labour"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1900">Christi martyris Vincencii</orgName>,
                        situm in <rs key="#Fines #Abbots #Monasteries">territorio</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Fines #Abbots #Monks #Monasteries #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#estates/1902">Beneventano</geogName>, super <rs key="#Rivers"
                            >fluvium</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/609">Vulturnum</placeName>, nostram
                        adiens celsitudinem, detulit <rs key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">precepta</rs>
                        precessorum nostrorum imperatorum, et <rs key="#Emperor/king">regum</rs>,
                        videlicet <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/249"
                            >Desiderii</persName>, <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/14"
                            >Caroli</persName> , <persName key="#Emperor/king" ref="#people/118"
                            >Lodovici</persName> , atque <persName key="#Emperor/king"
                            ref="#people/9">Lotharii</persName>, per quem contulerunt ex suis rebus
                        in prefatum monasterium, ac confirmaverunt res et possessiones ibi a
                        principibus, ducibus, reliquisque fidelibus collatas. Unde prefatus abbas
                        nostram exoravit clemenciam, ut eadem precepta, ac legales scripciones, nec
                        non predia per diversas fines regni Italici coniacencia eidem cenobio
                        collata, per nostre <rs key="#Imperial/royal_diploma">confirmacionis
                            preceptum</rs>, in prefatum venerabilem locum concederemus, et
                        confirmaremus. Cuius peticionibus faventes, pro Dei amore, animarumque
                        nostrarum remedio, per hoc nostre confirmacionis preceptum, prout iuste, et
                        legaliter possumus, concedimus, et confirmamus, ac penitus corroboramus in
                        predicto cenobio Christi martiris Vincencii omnia precepta precessorum
                        nostrorum imperatorum et regum, videlicet Desiderii, Caroli, Lodovici, atque
                        Lotharii, verumtamen omnes res et possessiones per diversos fines regni
                        Italici positas per eadem precepta, vel quolibet legales scripciones a
                        principibus, ducibus, reliquisque fidelibus ibidem collatas, nec non
                        monasteria et cellas inferius nominatas, primitus videlicet declarantes
                        ipsas hereditates, que circumdant ipsum monasterium, per has quoque fines:
                        incipiente itaque a <rs key="#Rivers">fluvio</rs>, qui dicitur <placeName
                            key="#Rivers" ref="#places/2323">Sangro</placeName>, deinde per
                            <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                            ref="#places/2814">montes puplicos</placeName> usque in <rs
                            key="#Mountains">monte</rs>, qui dicitur <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/2324">Azze</placeName>, et sic revolvente monte eodem usque
                        in <rs key="#Rivers">fluvio</rs>, qui dicitur <placeName key="#Rivers"
                            ref="#places/2327">Melfa</placeName>, et quemadmodum decurrit ipsa Melfa
                        usque ubi coniungit se cum parvo <rs key="#Rivers">fluvio</rs>, qui dicitur
                            <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/2813">Mellarino</placeName>, et
                        abhinc in vertice <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            >montis</rs>, qui dicitur Barbola, et sic per cilium montis eiusdem
                        usque in montem Archanum, et montem Marthe, montemque <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/2325">Casale</placeName>, eosque videlicet montes
                        extrinsecus circumdantes in ortum usque <rs key="#Rivers">riaginis</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/2309">Ravennola</placeName> qui
                        nominatur, et a capite eiusdem riaginis venientes iuxta <rs
                            key="#Mountains #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention">montes
                            puplicos</rs> in montem usque <placeName
                            key="#Mountains #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/2326">Benafranam</placeName>, qui est super <placeName
                            key="#Cities" ref="#places/2300">urbem</placeName>; eodem vero
                        revolvente monte usque in cilium montis, qui est super <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">terram</rs>, que vocatur <geogName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#estates/1929">Arcora</geogName>, que est <rs key="#Churches"
                            >ecclesia</rs> hereditas [...] <orgName
                            key="#Landed_possessions #Churches #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1904">Dei genitricis Marie</orgName>, que
                            <placeName
                            key="#Churches #Landed_possessions #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Function #Redistributive #Outflow #Allocation_to_churches"
                            ref="#places/2330">Olivetum</placeName> vocatur, subiecta prephati
                        monasterii, et <rs key="#Churches">ecclesie</rs> nichilominus hereditas
                            <orgName key="#Churches #Landed_possessions"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1910">Sancte Cristine</orgName>, subdita eiusdem
                        cenobii, cum inclitis <rs key="#Landed_possessions">territoriis</rs> suis,
                        et cum reliquis finibus ipsa hereditas circumdata in <rs
                            key="#Rivers">fluvio</rs> usque <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/609">Vulturno</placeName>;
                        nam iterum ex alia parte inchoante a prima fine cum iam dicto fluvio Sangro,
                        ipsoque relinquente quomodo decernit aparum colle, et pergens usque in <rs
                            key="#Rivers">fluvio</rs>, qui dicitur <placeName key="#Rivers"
                            ref="#places/2328">Foruli</placeName>, eodemque decurrente fluvio usque
                        in <rs key="#Rivers">fluvio</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers" ref="#places/2329">Vuantra</placeName>, et quomodo
                        decurrit ipsum fluvium in alio flumine, quod Vulturnus vocatur, et
                        quemammodum ipsum decurrit flumen iuxta terras eiusdem monasterii usque in
                        predictis finibus, et <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terris</rs> ecclesie
                        Sancte Marie. Per has quoque fines, una cum servis, et ancillis,
                        cespitibusque suis, necnon et cum <rs key="#Castle">castris</rs>, montibus,
                        collibus, vallibus, toronibus, ecclesiis, <rs key="#Rivers #Riverbed"
                            >aquis</rs>, <rs key="#Animals #Hay/fodder">pascuis</rs>, et omnia infra
                        ipsis finibus manencia, ac nostra presenti auctoritate, in prephato
                        monasterio concedimus et confirmamus, sicut iam dudum repperimus in predicto
                        cenobio concessum, et confirmatum esse a domno Lodovico serenissimo
                        imperatore per sigillatum preceptum. Interea concedimus insuper, et
                        confirmamus in eodem monasterio siquidem <rs key="#Monasteries"
                            >monasterium</rs> in honore <orgName key="#Monasteries"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1967">beati Petri apostoli</orgName>
                        constructum, positum in loco <placeName key="#Monasteries"
                            ref="#places/2357">Trite</placeName>, <rs key="#Fines">territorio</rs>
                        <geogName key="#Fines #Monasteries" ref="#estates/313"
                            >Vualvense</geogName>; et in <placeName
                            key="#Cells/hermitages #Slave #Slave_labour #Landed_possessions #Rivers"
                            ref="#places/1820">Penne</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs> unam, que nunccupatur <orgName
                            key="#Cells/hermitages #Slave #Slave_labour #Landed_possessions"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1974">Sancta Maria in Musano</orgName>; in
                        Abruzo <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs> unam in loco, qui vocatur
                            <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#places/2806">Arole</placeName>;
                        item <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1956">Sancta
                            Maria in Duas Basilicas</orgName> iuxta <placeName
                            key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#places/2323">Sangrum</placeName>; seu et
                            <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterium</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1940">Sancte
                            Marie</orgName> in territorio Marsicano, quod situm est in loco
                        Apinianici; et in <rs key="#City_territory">finibus</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cities #City_territory #Cells/hermitages #Landed_possessions" ref="#places/2001">Sorane</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Cities">civitatis</rs> inclitam <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages #Landed_possessions" ref="#places/2819">vallem Soranam</placeName> cum omnibus
                        ecclesiis, et <rs key="#Landed_possessions">pertinenciis</rs> suis, et aliis
                        cum cellis, et terris in ipsis consistentibus partibus, subditis eiusdem
                        cenobii, per cognitas fines, sicut precepta eiusdem continent monasterii,
                        videlicet regum, principum, et ducum, seu aliorumque fidelium scripciones
                        ibidem ab ipsis collatas; sed <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1938">Sancte
                            Columbe</orgName>; <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages #Landed_possessions"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1939">Sancti Donati</orgName> in <placeName
                            key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#places/2358">Cominu</placeName>; <rs
                            key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages #Landed_possessions"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1941">Sancti Mauri</orgName> in <placeName
                            key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#places/2360">Anglone</placeName>; quam et
                        alias cellas, et <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terras</rs> in ipsis finibus;
                        sed <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1943">Sancte
                            Agathe</orgName> in loco <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#places/2362">Turcino</placeName>; <rs key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            >cellam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Cells/hermitages #Wine #Landed_possessions #Slave #Slave_labour"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1955">Sancti Petri</orgName> de <placeName
                            key="#Cells/hermitages #Slave #Slave_labour" ref="#places/177"
                            >Vairano</placeName>, cum omnibus <rs key="#Slave #Slave_labour"
                            >servis</rs>, et ancillis, cespitibus, <rs key="#Wine">vineis</rs>, et
                            <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terris</rs> in omnibus sicut eiusdem
                        monasterii continent scripciones; sed <rs key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            >cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1919"> Sancti
                            Salvatoris</orgName> de <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#places/112">Alife</placeName>; <rs key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            >cellam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1918">Sancti Martini</orgName> de <placeName
                            key="#Cells/hermitages #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Object"
                            ref="#places/2345">monte Marsico</placeName>; <rs
                            key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1919">Sancte
                            Crucis</orgName> ; <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1949">Sancti
                            Ylarii</orgName> ; <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1937">Sancti Petri
                            de Tontole</orgName>; <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1936">Sancti
                            Vincencii de Tremojola</orgName>, que est iuxta limitem; sed <rs
                            key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Gualdi #Forests #Other_basins #Landed_possessions #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Rivers #Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention 
                                    #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1933">Sancti Sossii</orgName> cum inclito <rs
                            key="#Gualdi">vualdo</rs> suo, in loco <placeName
                            key="#Cells/hermitages #Gualdi #Forests #Landed_possessions #Roads #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Other_basins"
                            ref="#places/605">Liburie</placeName>, ubi dicitur <placeName
                            key="#Cells/hermitages #Forests #Landed_possessions #Gualdi #Roads #Marshes/lagoons/tombolos #Other_basins"
                            ref="#places/2351">Pantanum</placeName> has fines habentes: a prima
                        parte decurrit <rs key="#Roads">via antiqua</rs>, que venit de Ducenta, que
                        decernit inter has <rs key="#Landed_possessions">terras</rs>, et vualdu, et
                        alias terras, et vualdu, quod fuit predicti monasterii, et qualiter
                        descendit via ipsa, et intrat in ipsum Pantanum, et silvam, et <rs
                            key="#Marshes/lagoons/tombolos">paludem</rs> prefati monasterii, que est
                        coniuncta <placeName>Laneo</placeName>; a secunda autem parte <rs
                            key="#Roads">via est antiqua</rs>, que dicitur <rs key="#Roads"
                            >Vicana</rs>; a tercia vero iterum usque ad viam, que fuit antiqua, que
                        vadit ad ipsam <rs key="#Other_basins">piscinam</rs> iam dicti monasterii,
                        et decernit vias ipsas terras, et vualdu antedicti monasterii, et aliam <rs
                            key="#Roads">terram</rs> prefati cenobii, que dicitur de <geogName
                            key="#Landed_possessions" ref="#estates/1926">Tortora</geogName>, et
                        terras aliorum hominum, que ibi affines sunt, et sicut incipit super ipsam
                        piscinam, et qualiter revolvit circa ipsam terram de eodem vualdo, et iam
                        dictam terram, que dicitur de Tortora, et vadit ad ipsum Pantanum predicti
                        monasterii, et qualiter vadit et pergens per ipsum Pantanum, et <rs
                            key="#Forests">silvam</rs>, et paludem usque in ipsum
                            <placeName>Frigidum</placeName>; a quarta autem parte usque in iam
                        dictum Frigidum, et predictum Laneum cum omnibus, que infra has fines
                        consistent vel manent; sed <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1932">Sancti
                            Vincencii</orgName> infra <rs key="#Cities">civitatem</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages #Cities" ref="#places/2350"
                            >Neapolim</placeName>; <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1934">Sancti
                            Vincencii</orgName> de <placeName key="Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#places/2356">Cume</placeName>; <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1922">Sancti Petri</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs> iuxta <rs key="#Cities"
                            >civitatem</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#places/110"
                            >Beneventanam</placeName>, prope <rs key="#Rivers">fluvio</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Rivers #Cells/hermitages" ref="#places/2348"
                            >Sabbati</placeName>; <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName
                            key="#Fiscal_property #Textual_occurrence #Mention #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1908">Sancte Marie de Castaneto</orgName>, que
                        est in <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#places/2321">castro
                            Piniano</placeName>; <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1997">Sancti
                            Marci</orgName> de <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#places/2817"
                            >Petra Cutilia</placeName>; <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages #Casalia" ref="#juridical_persons/1929"
                            >Sancti Petri de Vipera</orgName> cum ipso <rs key="#Casalia"
                            >casale</rs>, qui dicitur <geogName key="#Casalia" ref="#estates/1917"
                            >Leoni</geogName>; <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1928">Sancte
                            Marie</orgName> de <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#places/2352"
                            >Planisi</placeName>; <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1926">Sancti
                            Iohannis</orgName> de <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#places/2349">Lucere</placeName>; <rs key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            >cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1996">Sancte
                            Marie</orgName> de <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#places/2815"
                            >Quinque Milia</placeName>; <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1948">Sancti
                            Vincencii</orgName> de <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#places/111">Telese</placeName>; <rs key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            >cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages #Mills" ref="#juridical_persons/1927">Sancti
                            Iohannis</orgName> de <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#places/554">Lisine</placeName> cum ipsa <rs key="#Mills"
                            >molina</rs>; <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1942">Sancti
                            Eleutheri</orgName> in <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#places/2361">Fundiliano</placeName>; <rs key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            >cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Fiscal_property #Mention #Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1901">Sancte Marie</orgName> de <placeName
                            key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#places/2301">Loco Sano</placeName> ; <rs
                            key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1930">Sancti
                            Vincencii</orgName> de <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#places/2354">Tocco</placeName>; <rs key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            >cellam</rs> infra <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages #Cities"
                            ref="#places/84">Salernitanam</placeName>
                        <rs key="#Cities">civitatem</rs> in honore <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1925">sancti Georgii</orgName> constructam, cum
                        omnibus suis pertinenciis; <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages" ref="#juridical_persons/1959">Sancti
                            Valentini</orgName> in <rs key="#Rivers">fluvio</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages #Rivers" ref="#places/2370"
                            >Bixentino</placeName>; <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1957">Sancti Vincencii</orgName>
                        <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs> in <rs key="#Rivers">fluvio</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages #Rivers" ref="#places/2369"
                            >Tusciano</placeName>; <rs key="#Cells/hermitages">cellam</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Cells/hermitages #Landed_possessions"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/1960">Sancti Vincencii</orgName> in <rs
                            key="#Rivers">fluvio</rs>
                        <placeName key="#Cells/hermitages #Rivers" ref="#places/2305"
                            >Tensa</placeName>, et omnia ad iam dictam abbaciam <rs
                            key="#Landed_possessions">pertinencia</rs>, cum omnibus aliis cappellis
                        et pertinenciis earum, cum <rs key="#Castle">castellis</rs>, <rs
                            key="#Villas">villis</rs>, <rs key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casis,
                            massariciis</rs>, <rs key="#Mansi">mansis</rs>, <rs key="#Forests"
                            >silvis</rs>, <rs key="#Hay/fodder #Animals">pascuis</rs>, venacionibus,
                            <rs key="#Fisheries #Fish">piscacionibus</rs>, <rs key="#Wine"
                            >vineis</rs>, arbustis, pratis, <rs key="#Slave #Slave_labour"
                            >servis</rs>, ancillis, <rs key="#Aldius">aldionibus</rs>, aldianis,
                        redivicionibus, nec non cum omnibus, que dici et nominari possit in prefato
                        monasterio concedimus, et confirmamus. Ea videlicet racione, quatinus
                        prenominatus abbas, et suis successores de omnibus castellis, et capellis
                        [...], vel monasteriis tam in hoc precepto, quamque in aliis preceptis,
                        offercionibus, atque scripcionibus, que continere videtur, habeant
                        potestatem tenendi, iuste commutandi, ordinandi, regulariter instruendi, vel
                        quicquid iustum [...], visum fuerit faciendi, absque omni contradiccione
                        quorumlibet hominum. Sancimus insuper, et nostra imperiali institucione
                        corroboramus, ut si aliquo in tempore fuerit orta contencio de rebus iam
                        dicti monasterii, nullus audeat deinceps per parentum possessiones ipsas
                        hereditates residere, vel contendere presumat, excepto per verissimas
                        cartulas, et iustas consignaciones. Verumtamen statuimus atque firmamus, ob
                        amorem eterne vite, et oracionibus fratrum, quorum preces annuimus, ut ipsam
                        semper legem per annorum curricula pars predicti cenobii accipiat de omnibus
                        suis territoriis ab omnibus hominibus, quam instituit <persName
                            key="#Emperor/king #Juridical_sources #Lex" ref="#people/48"
                            >Astulfus</persName>
                        <rs key="#Emperor/king">rex Langobardorum</rs> De ecclesiis. Nam ex ea
                        quoque re lex alia nec recipiatur, nec [...] qualibet ulterius iudicetur
                        persona. Si vero fuerit contencio de servis, vel de alia quacumque re, inter
                        aliquem vicinum suum, seu qualecumque hominem, liceat eis se defendere,
                        sicut prisca consuetudo fuit per scariones eiusdem monasterii, nec audeat
                        alicuis ipsos abbates, vel monachos ad sacramentum invitare, quia contra
                        divinam auctoritatem et [...] regulam est. Precipientes insuper iubemus ut
                            <rs key="#Immunity">nullus</rs> rex, dux, princeps, marchio, comes,
                        vicecomes, gastaldeus, sculdascius, vet aliquis publice rei exactor iam
                        dictum abbatem, vei suos successores, aut monachos ex eius cenobio, vel eius
                        cellis inquietare, laniare de prediis monasterii, aut aliquibus rebus
                        disvestire [...], aut per placita secularia ducere, recepimus preterea
                        pretextatum monasterium cum omnibus pretextatis monasteriis, ac cellis,
                        rebus quoque, ac familiis ibidem aspicientibus cum fratribus, ac monachis
                        ibidem Deo famulantibus, sub nostre tuicionis munburdum. Concedimus quoque,
                        et corroboramus, <rs key="#Districtio">ut nullus</rs> ex servis, aut ex
                        familia eiusdem monasterii vel eos, qui cortisianas vocant audeat
                        inquietare, aut ad publicam, vel comitum placitum ducere, aut iudicare,
                        neque in domibus vel casis eiusdem monasterii iudicium, aut placitum tenere,
                        nisi abbas prefati monasterii, aut suus missus, ante cuius conspectum omnes
                        sui residentes, sicut ante nostram presenciam legem faciat et recipiat, <rs
                            key="#Tolls #Exemption">neque placiaticum, portaticum, pontanaticum,
                            casaticum, vel quodlibet pensum quisquam homo</rs>, aut publice rei
                        exactor tollere, aut exigere presumat, sed disponimus, ut abbates et
                        prepositi eiusdem loci, iuxta priscam consuetudinem ad communem utilitatem
                        fratrum sua disponant providencia, absque alicuius contradiccione. Si quis
                        igitur huius nostri precepti institucione, et confirmacionem, seu munburdi
                        tuicione aliquando infringere temptaverit, sciat se compositurum auri optimi
                        libras duomilia, medietatem Camere nostre, et medietatem parti predicti
                        monasterii. quod ut verius credatur, diligenciusque ab omnibus observetur,
                        manu propria roborantes anulo nostro insigniri iussimus). Signum domni
                        Henrici [M] serenissimi et invictissimi imperatoris augusti. <persName
                            key="#Chancellor"><name ref="Henricus">Henricus</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Chancellor">cancellarius</rs>, vice <persName
                            key="#Archchancellor #Bishops"><name ref="Everardus"
                            >Everardi</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Bishops">episcopi</rs> et <rs key="#Archchancellor"
                            >archicancellarii</rs>, recognovit. <date>Datum anno Dominice
                            incarnacionis millesimo XIIII, indiccione XII, anno domini Henrici
                            imperatoris augusti regni XII imperii eius I. Actum <placeName
                                key="#Cities" ref="#places/52">Rome</placeName></date>, feliciter,
                        amen.</ab>
                </div>
